    "type": "SensitivityAnalysis",
    "name": "One-at-a-time sensitivity analysis on FEA model inputs for non-cannulated compression-bending",
    "description": "Young's modulus (Ti-6Al-4V, ±5%), friction coefficient at screw–block interface (0.1–0.4), and mesh density (coarse/medium/fine) were each varied independently across their uncertainty ranges while holding all other parameters at nominal values. Construct stiffness exhibited the highest sensitivity to Young's modulus (±3.8% QoI change), yield force was most sensitive to friction coefficient (±6.1%), and force at 40 mm displacement was insensitive to mesh refinement beyond the medium discretization level (<0.4% change), confirming that mesh-induced error is not a dominant uncertainty source for this COU."
  },
